<br>
The illegal act here is fraud.  It's taking money as payment for something you promise to deliver, but then don't.  <br>
<br>
You can sue him in Colorado, or very likely in your home state.  Look at the procedures for general sessions or "people's court" lawsuits in your state (they vary).  Typically, you don't really need a lawyer to bring one of these actions, and the fee for serving process is built into the filing fee. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uthoggdlogg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ThoggDlogg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>THogg!</span><br>  Posts: 360<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/5/02 1:18:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2476.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   well I dunno </span><hr size=1> actualy .. it does violate verants legal right to its copyrighted intelectual property..<br>
